er the precious remark of mpakier (thanks!), I&#8217;ll remove a join and the query is 100-500 times faster: so the batch sending should be faster too. [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"alo";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1474:"<p>Here you are the new version <strong>2.2.1</strong> of EasyMail newsletter plugin.<br />\nThe new important feature is the <strong>fix of query that gets the recipients in queue on batch sending</strong>.<br />\nAfter the precious remark of <a href="http://www.eventualo.net/forum/topic/371">mpakier</a> (thanks!), I&#8217;ll remove a <em>join</em> and the query is 100-500 times faster: so the batch sending should be faster too.</p>\n<p>You can go on WP.org and <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/alo-easymail/">download it</a>.<br />\nThe upgrade will alter a plugin db table (adds a user_id column in recipients table), so: <strong>after upgrade files always remember to de-activate and activate it again.</strong><br />\nWarning: before upgrade, be sure to complete newsletters already on sending!</p>\n<p>You can use the <a href="http://www.eventualo.net/forum/">forum</a> to share your feedback. And you can contribute to keep the plugin update donating some money to me. </p>\n<form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post">\n<input name="cmd" type="hidden" value="_s-xclick" />\n<input name="lc" type="hidden" value="EN" />\n<input name="hosted_button_id" type="hidden" value="9E6BPXEZVQYHA" />\n<input style="border: 0pt none;" alt="PayPal" name="submit" src="https://www.paypal.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_SM.gif" type="image" /> <img src="https://www.paypal.com/it_IT/i/scr/pixel.gif" border="0" alt="" width="1